We'd like you to meet <b>Waterford</b>, this week's featured citizen!<br><br>Waterford moved to Millsberry on November 21, 2005. He felt like Lakeview was the neighborhood best suited for his easygoing nature. Waterford moved into his <a href='/home/?user=p0_k0n9'>92788 Lakewood</a> residence where he's still enjoying the waterfront breezes today.<br><br>When you see Waterford, you shouldn't be surprised if he has his eyes to the stars. His passion for looking to the heavens earned him a Gold Junior Astronomer's trophy. Waterford stretches before his stargazing to prevent neck cramps. He usually does extra warming up if he's expecting shooting stars.<br><br>Next time you're in Lakeview, stop by and check out Waterford's digs. Don't be alarmed if he's not there, he's probably just working on his Hide and Seek technique. Practice makes perfect, and Waterford has the Hide and Seek trophy to prove it. If you don't find him, chances are he'll find you.<br><br>When Waterford isn't scouting hiding spots, he likes to tickle the ivory on his impressive pipe organ. You'll not only hear scales, but see them as well. There's a Golden Serpent right next to his musical equipment. <br><br>Next time you see Waterford, shake his hand and give him a pat on the back for being such an outstanding citizen. <br></div>
